
# 2017-11-11 

Transfer markdown to HTML with python, 
make easy to adjust color, font size,
make it less depend on server functions,
js, css might be used in html pages.

copy a lot from ../py

# install
 

    # python, use env 'test' in this machine, source ~/py/test/bin/activate
    pip install markdown pystache

    # for local npm links
    npm install
    cd ~/workspace/page.color
    npm link
    cd ~/workspace/gg.intro/pyb/config
    npm link page.color


## pystache/mustache template

    use {{{ instead of {{, if not to escape html tage 


# files

    mkmd.py : 
        transfer markdown to html
        need to run in command line offer: -s -t
        source and target
        make sure python env 'test' which has pystache

    compile_js_css.py   
        js and css compile

    mkindex.py
        make index.html and index.cn.html from
        intro.md and cn/intro.md
        
    ...

